  <div class="faq">
    <details>
      <summary>Why use a DCF for a bank?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">While not traditional for banks due to the nature of their working capital and debt, a DCF can still highlight the underlying cash generation of fee-heavy businesses like custody banks. However, the resulting absolute valuation should be viewed with extreme caution due to the "Net Cash" inflation mentioned above.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Why 9% discount rate?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">The discount rate represents the required return. For a systemically important custody bank with highly recurring revenues, the risk profile is lower than an average industrial company or a traditional lending bank, justifying a slightly lower discount rate.</div>
    </details>
